{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28b672394ffe2uI216TSFvnXtq","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d7498dcee001vFSESYQXuYlorA","parts":[{"id":"prt_d7498ed22001qxCWMeGYaA8FHv","messageID":"msg_d7498dcee001vFSESYQXuYlorA","sessionID":"ses_28b672394ffe2uI216TSFvnXtq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f2f9bcc227504fc3a08905db","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # tmuxp\n2: \n3: Session manager for tmux, which allows users to save and load tmux sessions through simple configuration files. Powered by [libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux).\n4: \n5: [![Python Package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/tmuxp.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/tmuxp/)\n6: [![Docs](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/docs/badge.svg)](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/)\n7: [![Build status](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/tests/badge.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/actions?query=workflow%3A%22tests%22)\n8: [![Code Coverage](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp)\n9: [![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/tmux-python/tmuxp.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/LICENSE)\n10: \n11: **New to tmux?** [The Tao of tmux](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux)\n12: is available on Leanpub and [Amazon Kindle](http://amzn.to/2gPfRhC).\n13: Read and browse the book for free [on the\n14: web](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux/read).\n15: \n16: **Have some spare time?** Help us triage and code review and the tracker. See [issue\n17: #290](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/discussions/290)!\n18: \n19: # Installation\n20: \n21: pip:\n22: \n23: ```console\n24: $ pip install --user tmuxp\n25: ```\n26: \n27: If you're managing the project with [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/), add tmuxp as a dependency instead:\n28: \n29: ```console\n30: $ uv add tmuxp\n31: ```\n32: \n33: To run tmuxp without installing it globally, similar to `pipx`, invoke it with\n34: [uvx](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/):\n35: \n36: ```console\n37: $ uvx tmuxp\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Homebrew:\n41: \n42: ```console\n43: $ brew install tmuxp\n44: ```\n45: \n46: Debian / ubuntu:\n47: \n48: ```console\n49: $ sudo apt install tmuxp\n50: ```\n51: \n52: Nix:\n53: \n54: ```console\n55: $ [[ -z $(which tmux) ]] && (nix-env -i tmux && nix-env -i tmuxp) || nix-env -i tmuxp\n56: ```\n57: \n58: Find the package for your distro on repology: <https://repology.org/project/tmuxp/versions>\n59: \n60: Developmental releases:\n61: \n62: - [pip](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/):\n63: \n64:   ```console\n65:   pip install --user --upgrade --pre tmuxp\n66:   ```\n67: \n68:   Or request the pre-release from a uv project environment:\n69: \n70:   ```console\n71:   uv add 'tmuxp>=1.10.0b1'\n72:   ```\n73: \n74: \n75: - [uvx](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/):\n76: \n77:   ```console\n78:   uvx tmuxp\n79:   ```\n80: \n81: - [pipx](https://pypa.github.io/pipx/docs/):\n82: \n83:   ```console\n84:   pipx install --suffix=@next 'tmuxp' --pip-args '\\--pre' --force\n85:   ```\n86: \n87:   Then use `tmuxp@next load [session]`.\n88: \n89: # Load a tmux session\n90: \n91: Load tmux sessions via json and YAML,\n92: [tmuxinator](https://github.com/aziz/tmuxinator) and\n93: [teamocil](https://github.com/remiprev/teamocil) style.\n94: \n95: ```yaml\n96: session_name: 4-pane-split\n97: windows:\n98:   - window_name: dev window\n99:     layout: tiled\n100:     shell_command_before:\n101:       - cd ~/ # run as a first command in all panes\n102:     panes:\n103:       - shell_command: # pane no. 1\n104:           - cd /var/log # run multiple commands in this pane\n105:           - ls -al | grep \\.log\n106:       - echo second pane # pane no. 2\n107:       - echo third pane # pane no. 3\n108:       - echo fourth pane # pane no. 4\n109: ```\n110: \n111: Save as _mysession.yaml_, and load:\n112: \n113: ```console\n114: tmuxp load ./mysession.yaml\n115: ```\n116: \n117: Projects with _.tmuxp.yaml_ or _.tmuxp.json_ load via directory:\n118: \n119: ```console\n120: tmuxp load path/to/my/project/\n121: ```\n122: \n123: Load multiple at once (in bg, offer to attach last):\n124: \n125: ```console\n126: tmuxp load mysession ./another/project/\n127: ```\n128: \n129: Name a session:\n130: \n131: ```console\n132: tmuxp load -s session_name ./mysession.yaml\n133: ```\n134: \n135: [simple](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#short-hand-inline-style) and\n136: [very\n137: elaborate](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#super-advanced-dev-environment)\n138: config examples\n139: \n140: # User-level configurations\n141: \n142: tmuxp checks for configs in user directories:\n143: \n144: - `$TMUXP_CONFIGDIR`, if set\n145: - `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, usually _$HOME/.config/tmuxp/_\n146: - `$HOME/.tmuxp/`\n147: \n148: Load your tmuxp config from anywhere by using the filename, assuming\n149: _\\~/.config/tmuxp/mysession.yaml_ (or _.json_):\n150: \n151: ```console\n152: $ tmuxp load mysession\n153: ```\n154: \n155: See [author's tmuxp configs](https://github.com/tony/tmuxp-config) and\n156: the projects'\n157: [tmuxp.yaml](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/.tmuxp.yaml).\n158: \n159: # Shell\n160: \n161: _New in 1.6.0_:\n162: \n163: `tmuxp shell` launches into a python console preloaded with the attached\n164: server, session, and window in\n165: [libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux) objects.\n166: \n167: ```console\n168: $ tmuxp shell\n169: \n170: (Pdb) server\n171: <libtmux.server.Server object at 0x7f7dc8e69d10>\n172: (Pdb) server.sessions\n173: [Session($1 your_project)]\n174: (Pdb) session\n175: Session($1 your_project)\n176: (Pdb) session.name\n177: 'your_project'\n178: (Pdb) window\n179: Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project))\n180: (Pdb) window.name\n181: 'your_window'\n182: (Pdb) window.panes\n183: [Pane(%6 Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project)))\n184: (Pdb) pane\n185: Pane(%6 Window(@3 1:your_window, Session($1 your_project))\n186: ```\n187: \n188: Supports [PEP\n189: 553](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0553/) `breakpoint()`\n190: (including `PYTHONBREAKPOINT`). Also supports direct commands via `-c`:\n191: \n192: ```console\n193: $ tmuxp shell -c 'print(window.name)'\n194: my_window\n195: \n196: $ tmuxp shell -c 'print(window.name.upper())'\n197: MY_WINDOW\n198: ```\n199: \n200: Read more on [tmuxp shell](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/cli/shell/) in\n201: the CLI docs.\n202: \n203: # Pre-load hook\n204: \n205: Run custom startup scripts (such as installing project dependencies)\n206: before loading tmux. See the\n207: [before_script](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/configuration/examples/#bootstrap-project-before-launch)\n208: example\n209: \n210: # Load in detached state\n211: \n212: You can also load sessions in the background by passing `-d` flag\n213: \n214: # Screenshot\n215: \n216: <img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/master/docs/_static/tmuxp-demo.gif\" class=\"align-center\" style=\"width:45.0%\" alt=\"image\" />\n217: \n218: # Freeze a tmux session\n219: \n220: Snapshot your tmux layout, pane paths, and window/session names.\n221: \n222: ```console\n223: $ tmuxp freeze session-name\n224: ```\n225: \n226: See more about [freezing\n227: tmux](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/cli/freeze/) sessions.\n228: \n229: # Convert a session file\n230: \n231: Convert a session file from yaml to json and vice versa.\n232: \n233: ```console\n234: $ tmuxp convert filename\n235: ```\n236: \n237: This will prompt you for confirmation and shows you the new file that is\n238: going to be written.\n239: \n240: You can auto confirm the prompt. In this case no preview will be shown.\n241: \n242: ```console\n243: $ tmuxp convert -y filename\n244: $ tmuxp convert --yes filename\n245: ```\n246: \n247: # Plugin System\n248: \n249: tmuxp has a plugin system to allow for custom behavior. See more about\n250: the [Plugin System](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/topics/plugins/).\n251: \n252: # Debugging Helpers\n253: \n254: The `load` command provides a way to log output to a log file for\n255: debugging purposes.\n256: \n257: ```console\n258: $ tmuxp load --log-file <log-file-name> .\n259: ```\n260: \n261: Collect system info to submit with a Github issue:\n262: \n263: ```console\n264: $ tmuxp debug-info\n265: ------------------\n266: environment:\n267:     system: Linux\n268:     arch: x86_64\n269: \n270: # ... so on\n271: ```\n272: \n273: # Docs / Reading material\n274: \n275: See the [Quickstart](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/quickstart/).\n276: \n277: [Documentation](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com) homepage (also in\n278: [中文](http://tmuxp-zh.rtfd.org/))\n279: \n280: Want to learn more about tmux itself? [Read The Tao of Tmux\n281: online](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/about_tmux/).\n282: \n283: # Donations\n284: \n285: Your donations fund development of new features, testing and support.\n286: Your money will go directly to maintenance and development of the\n287: project. If you are an individual, feel free to give whatever feels\n288: right for the value you get out of the project.\n289: \n290: See donation options at <https://tony.sh/support.html>.\n291: \n292: # Project details\n293: \n294: - tmux support: 3.2+\n295: - python support: >= 3.10, pypy, pypy3\n296: - Source: <https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp>\n297: - Docs: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com>\n298: - API: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/internals/api/>\n299: - Changelog: <https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/history/>\n300: - Issues: <https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/issues>\n301: - Test Coverage: <https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp>\n302: - pypi: <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/tmuxp>\n303: - Open Hub: <https://www.openhub.net/p/tmuxp-python>\n304: - Repology: <https://repology.org/project/tmuxp/versions>\n305: - License: [MIT](http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).\n\n(End of file - total 305 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# tmuxp\n\nSession manager for tmux, which allows users to save and load tmux sessions through simple configuration files. Powered by [libtmux](https://github.com/tmux-python/libtmux).\n\n[![Python Package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/tmuxp.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/tmuxp/)\n[![Docs](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/docs/badge.svg)](https://tmuxp.git-pull.com/)\n[![Build status](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/workflows/tests/badge.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/actions?query=workflow%3A%22tests%22)\n[![Code Coverage](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp/branch/master/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/tmux-python/tmuxp)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/tmux-python/tmuxp.svg)](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/blob/master/LICENSE)\n\n**New to tmux?** [The Tao of tmux](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux)\nis available on Leanpub and [Amazon Kindle](http://amzn.to/2gPfRhC).\nRead and browse the book for free [on the\nweb](https://leanpub.com/the-tao-of-tmux/read).\n\n**Have some spare time?** Help us triage and code review and the tracker. See [issue\n#290](https://github.com/tmux-python/tmuxp/discussions/290)!\n\n# Installation\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775777672772,"end":1775777672789}}}]}
